The building itself was narrow but stretched four stories up. The architect was either a madman or a genius. Copper, brass, and rusted iron pipes wrapped themselves around the building, or if you observe it for long enough, you'll see they *were* the building. Steam, powders, and an array of fluids flew through these channels wailing and whistling as they made things rotate and reel in ways not entirely abiding by the laws of physics. The bottom floor had large windows through which you could make out even more bussing machinery. The door revolved swiftly on a massive cog with a note that read: "Please direct all rental requests to the borrow handler.".
